storyInfo: On the eve of the storm, there are reunions, and there are partings.

attributes.content: Guard this place.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: Watch your formation, keep an eye on her movements.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: You know who it is we're facing. Don't be like those stupid mercs.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: ...Here she comes.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: Watch her hands.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: She could draw her sword at anyâ€”
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: Watch the lights and shadows. Don't try to follow the sword.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: The Sarkaz with white horns silently carries her sword in her arms.
Wordlessly, she keeps moving forward.
The guards instinctively step back.
Hold your ground!
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: She stops.
Under the gaze of the guards, she raises her left hand, and takes out a small piece of paper from within her tattered robe.
I came as appointed, as he wished. No need to be on guard.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: Which way to Riverbank Street?
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: Shining!
What are you doing standing there? Get out of the way! I told you we had a family meeting today.
Understood.
attributes.name: Confessarius Guard

attributes.content: What took you so long, Shining? I've been waiting!
...Salus.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: It's not time yet.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: No, it's not. The leader won't be angry.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Come in, dinner's ready. Look at you. Have you not had anything decent to eat since you left Londinium?
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: I've talked to the leader. Tonight's menu is being prepared to Royal Victorian Academy of Sciences banquet standards.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Oh, Shining, Shining! How long has it been since the old days, when we used to chat at the dinner table? Tell me what you've seen and heard!
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Leader, Shining's back!
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Welcome.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: Sit. This is your place. We just came to Londinium then... it was a long time ago.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: It has been empty ever since you killed those poor souls and fled with the test subject.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: That betrayal chilled the clan to the bone.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: But I don't blame you. Sit.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: I can't wait. I've hardly had a good meal lately, staying all night in the labs.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: She pulls a chair and sits by the right hand side of the white-horned Confessarius leader.
He stops speaking and sits with his eyes half-closed.
A moment later, Shining puts down her sword and walks toward the only chair that is empty by the long table.
Talk about your experiments, Salus.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: Work at the dinner table? Alright, alright.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: There isn't much to talk about. I'm doing my best to extract emotions from memories, but the voices of the dead don't linger long on my fingertips.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: I've gotten some results, but only fragments. I'm running into a bottleneck.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: The information is like branches cut from their tree. You can reconstruct the shape of the tree, but a tree can't survive without its roots, much less grow new sprouts.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: And I can't capture voices from further before, never mind bringing them back to the present.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Like time, life only goes in one direction. A description of its nature must necessarily be abstract and literary. Even the Originium Arts of you and Shining can only capture an instant.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: The King of Sarkaz is the exception.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: That knowledge and the technique are like a waterfall, yet we can never find its source, or draw fresh water from it.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: My research has stalled since Shining's experiments stopped.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: What about you, Leader? Is the Regent planning something big? You've been spending most of your time at Westhaleg or The Shard; you hardly come to my lab anymore.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: The Regent's plan is at a crucial stage.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: I'm not sure I understand.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: From Kazdel to Kazdel, the Confessarii's service to those in power has always been one of pure mutual gain.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: But you've been so close to the Regent that people on the outside are beginning to think the Confessarius is the Regent's lieutenant.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Since when have we cared, Salus?
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: This is hardly the first time they've misunderstood the Confessarii.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: What's different about Theresis?
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: I would not recommend saying that name within earshot of General Manfred.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: That's why I'm doing it in front of family.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Like his predecessor, he came from no royal court, and his bloodline is far less pure than yours or Shining's.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: None of their ancestors have ever caught the Confessarii's attention. We've never gathered memories from their bloodlines.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Even if the King of Sarkaz chose his sister, it does not mean that her brother...
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Just as I've told you, Salus.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: Power comes from blood. Blood inherits memory. Memory accumulates sin. Sin forms shackles. Only those unbound by history can truly unshackle power.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: Alright, alright. May the glory of old return to the land under their majestic guidance.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: No, Salus.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: Succeed or fail, the Regent will make an impact on the Sarkaz. This is what is most frequently ignored.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: By the way, the test subject you took... what's her name again? Lisa? Liz? How's she doing?
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: ...Liz is doing fine.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: Is Oripathy taking its toll on her?
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: She is... unusual. Even if Dame Kal'tsit is at... at... at that medical institution you found, they may not be able to truly help her.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: It's good that she's back in Londinium. Your lab's still here with everything. You can bring her back anytime.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Is the food not to your taste, my dear sister?
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: It's been such a long time since you've been home. Speak up.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: If this is about Liz... I apologize. But you know Liz is not your average Infected.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Who's responsible for her suffering and consciousness? Who's responsible for her pain and memories? Can you continue to get along after she remembers all that?
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: She's not family. You have toâ€”
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: â€”She's my family.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: But... but she's going to become an empty shell if you don't come back to us. Don't forget why she was built that way.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: If you really care for her, I hope the end won't be too painful. Come back.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: I'm sure you understand.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: You understand. That's why you answered my invitation, isn't it?
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: From Originium to the truth of the King of Sarkaz. We've reached a clearer conclusion.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: She's simply an old cage. We could build a new one, if we had to...
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: Enough.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: Sigh.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: I've never seen you really angry, even when you hurt your own colleagues and took the girl.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: I guess I don't need to ask what you went through, all these years. What I can see is that...
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: You see outsiders as more important than family.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Salus empties her cup, which contained only water.
There was no wine. She does not like drinking, especially at work.
Her shadow sways under the light. This was not supposed to be a work day.
You're not my family.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: Haven't I made that clear enough?
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: You have.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: Shining does not look at the untouched food, or the other two Confessarii by her side.
She simply stands up, holding her sword in her arms.
I've asked the men watching Liz to leave.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: There's no need to send me any more invitations.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: The next time we meet... I expect it'll be in battle.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: 'Asked them to leave.'
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: Shining... you really think you're going to just leave like this?
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: There's nothing left for us to talk about.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: What if I said I don't want you to leave?
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: You can't stop me.
attributes.name: Shining

attributes.content: I think I can make you stay and chat for a little longer.
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: No?
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: The leader of the Confessarii silently sips his wine.
Shining can feel Salus activate her Arts. She could leave by pulling her sword, but what would happen then?
Will that really help her save Liz?
Shining.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: Leader! I wasn't really about to use force against Shining. Why did you stop me?
attributes.name: Salus

attributes.content: I've allowed you to act on your own.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: I've allowed you to be absent from my side.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: But do not interfere with the Regent's plans. Do not hinder the Sarkaz path to our long-awaited future.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: Shining, my sister.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: No one can truly break free from her bloodline, no matter how much she might detest it, how much she might desire to break those shackles.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: It is meaningless to try to deny the gift of blood.
attributes.name: Confessarius

attributes.content: ...I thought you already knew.
attributes.name: Shining
Shining
attributes.content: Not everything will go according to your plan...

attributes.name: Shining
attributes.content: Father.
attributes.joined: Not everything will go according to your plan...Father.

attributes.content: ...Your Highness.
attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou

attributes.content: My, my, Lettou. Why such a frown on your face?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Is the wine not good enough for you? Or is the flavor of the food too light?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Good wine should be paired with the futile resistance of the weak against fate, and the arrogance of heroes who drown in prophecy.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Even I am amazed at how they write their own stories for their own entertainment. Unfortunately, our Victorian friends are too reliant on fiction.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: We've seen better stuff, have we not, Lettou?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: I just saw you feed a nobleman's wife and children to your troops.
attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou
Lt. Colonel Lettou
attributes.content: I support the vetting of potential insurgents, but...

attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou
attributes.content: Er...
attributes.joined: I support the vetting of potential insurgents, but...Er...

attributes.content: Ughâ€“â€“!
attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou

attributes.text: His voice dies in his throat.
It is as though all the blood in his body has been forced to his esophagus. He falls to his knees and opens his mouth in desperation, but cannot find any air.
A blood mist comes over his vision. He sees the Vampire still sitting in his place, elegant and calm, not even bothering to look at him.

attributes.content: Lt. Colonel!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Form up! Protect the commander!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: You'll fight me here?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: That's not what the taste of your blood tells me.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Fear... worry.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: They're screaming for you to back off, to run away.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: ...Hold the line!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: The lips of the soldiers are as pale as their faces.
They hold their weapons with trembling handsâ€”sabers, bows, what Victoria has made for them.
They are the finest soldiers, unafraid of the Streltsy of Ursus, the Arts of Leithanien, or the broadside guns of Columbia.
But they are afraid of the Sarkaz sitting before them.
Put down your weapons...
attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou

attributes.content: Stand... stand down...
attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou

attributes.content: Lt. Colonel...
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: This is an order...
attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou

attributes.content: Yes... sir.
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: The soldiers back off in an orderly manner.
It took all of Lettou's strength to give the order. He stops resisting and accepts the eternal darkness that the Sarkaz has prepared for him.
Then, he hears the silky voice again.
Lettou, Lettou.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: I thought we were friends. Friends should trust each other, shouldn't they?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: I think I've been kind, overlooking those little extra-curricular activities of you and your men.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Deals under the table, black markets in the alleys... I've turned a blind eye to them because I don't think greed and desire should be punished.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: But I expect the same trust in return.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Many Gaulish nobles keep fowlbeasts as pets, building jeweled cages for the adorable things, lying them down on soft and delicate cushions.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: All the fowlbeasts need to do is squawk, and they'll be served the finest food.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: When the fowlbeasts are in a bad mood and peck their masters, their masters eagerly tell people of the intelligence and personality of their fowlbeasts.
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: But do you think the fowlbeasts have tamed their masters?
attributes.name: Sanguinarch of Vampires

attributes.content: Air returns to Lettou's lungs.
It takes him some time to stand again, his limbs still trembling, but he does his best to keep that trembling out of his voice.
Thank you for your mercy, Your Highness.
attributes.name: Lt. Colonel Lettou

attributes.content: March! March!
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: Stay in line!
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: I heard you were looking for me.
attributes.name: Hoederer

attributes.content: How are your injuries?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Same as ever. Won't interfere with the mission.
attributes.name: Hoederer

attributes.content: Good.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: I just got a message. Here.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Let me see.
attributes.name: Hoederer

attributes.content: Lost contact with the mercs sent to Highbury?
attributes.name: Hoederer

attributes.content: They should have been in communication an hour ago.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: The Military Commission is dissatisfied with the recent performance of the mercenaries.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Soldiers must pay attention to a greater battlefield. The Regent and I had... high hopes... for the mercenaries.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: I'll find out what happened to them.
attributes.name: Hoederer

attributes.content: No need. I've made arrangements.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: There's a possibility that they ran into an old acquaintance of yours.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Who could be as concerned about the Sarkaz supply lines as we ourselves?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Let me guess, Dr. {@nickname} and Ascalon...
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Are they investigating the Highbury munitions factories, or are they already preparing to attack other hubs with information about the supply lines?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Tend to your injuries, mercenary.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: You don't need any more 'wounds' before I find your old friends, one by one.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Doctor! You're here!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Did you get the intel from the factory?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.options: Some potential depots.;Half of the puzzle.

attributes.content: Not bad. I was thinking what I would have to do to extract you and Feist if something went wrong.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.options: We had Ascalon.;......;We've got Ascalon to thank.
One more thing, Ascalon.;Can I ask you another favor, Ascalon?
Can you reach W?;W is in Highbury, right?

attributes.content: She operates on her own devices.
attributes.name: Ascalon

attributes.options: That young Sarkaz mercenary...;The Sarkaz mercenary who wouldn't hurt the worker...

attributes.content: ...W will know.
attributes.name: Ascalon

attributes.options: Closure, did you see...;Is it the appointed time?

attributes.content: Doctor!
You turn around at the voice.
You see a familiar sight coming towards you.
We're here.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Yes... same here...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: When you suggested that we split up a few days ago, I knew it was the right call, but...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: At least we came back together alright. I'm so happy about that.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.options: What about your work, Closure?;Closure is key to tomorrow's operation.

attributes.content: Don't worry, I'm pretty well-prepared over here.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I don't know if the defenses share the same weaknesses across Londinium, but there must be common characteristics to the framework.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I've updated the drone's intrusion program based on intel from Misery and Horn, as well as the data taken from the artillery control room.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Get the drone close to the core of the Defense Force's command tower, and I can break into the system and access traffic records from the past ten days within thirty minutes.
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.options: Can you do it in twenty?;The quicker, the better.

attributes.content: Yeah... tomorrow will be a hard day.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: We've been probing the responses of the Sarkaz army within Londinium in the last few days.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: We expect Manfred and the Vampire to show up quickly. Ascalon, Logos and I will do our best to delay them.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: However...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.options: The longer it takes, the more dangerous it is.;We can't give Theresis time to react.

attributes.content: The Sarkaz of the Royal Court could appear at any time.
attributes.name: Ascalon

attributes.content: Yes, Doctor.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Dr. Kal'tsit is helping us delay the Nachzehrer and Lich, but there's only so much time she can buy.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.options: We can't handle multiple members of the Royal Court at once.;It could be very disadvantageous for us.
Watch the signal and be ready to pull out at a moment's notice.

attributes.content: Understood.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Rhodes Island and the Self-Salvation Corps are ready.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Allerdale, the mercenaries are looking for you.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Sorry, I was distracted. What did you say?
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: No, I'm the one who should apologize.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Maybe we could have saved Ailshie together, if I wasn't so anxious to leave.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: I know she's important to you.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: She's my only family.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: House Cumberland is no more.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: One woman does not make a family, eh?
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Maybe it was something that should have happened a long time ago, delayed until today.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Don't say that, Allerdale.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: That Vampire will be made to pay, I promise.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: The steam armor was lost in the fire. Maybe that's for the better. That way, I won't have to see it anymore.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: ...Vina.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Can you take me to the Glasgow Gang? I can pretend nothing ever happened.
attributes.name: Allerdale
Allerdale
attributes.content: I carry nothing on my shoulders. I'll just be your brain trust.

attributes.name: Allerdale
attributes.content: Sorry... I forgot you had Morgan.

attributes.name: Allerdale
attributes.content: I'll just be a thug then.
attributes.joined: I carry nothing on my shoulders. I'll just be your brain trust.Sorry... I forgot you had Morgan.I'll just be a thug then.

attributes.content: We'll bomb the Sarkaz camp together. You light a fire, and I'll kick their commander's arse once there's smoke.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: I'm joking.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: My path is long determined, Vina.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Why do you say that? You're still with us. The Glasgow Gang has more stories to write.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: So...
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: The answer is yes.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: I'll make sure you come back unharmed after kicking that commander's arse.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: That's my promise.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: I see... thanks.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Let's leave the jokes at that. I would begin to believe them if this went on.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Alright, I've got to go. Totter and the mercenaries are waiting for me. We need to double-check our route.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Get ready, Vina.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: The Sighs of Kings is before us.
attributes.name: Allerdale

attributes.content: Would you have said yes, if she truly invited you to leave?
Clovisia?
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: The walls of Londinium are tall. Few are able to escape their shadow.
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: But you did. You escaped the palace, and escaped Londinium. Perhaps Allerdale envies you because of that.
attributes.name: Clovisia
Clovisia
attributes.content: She has forced herself to carry the Cumberland name for twenty years.

attributes.name: Clovisia
attributes.content: But you're different. You thought about leaving your name behind, didn't you?
...I can't deny that.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: But I'm here now, regardless of what I thought.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Victoria is on the brink right now, and I must fight for her.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: ...Victoria.
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Kings, nobles, merchants, soldiers, workers...
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: People often use the word 'Victoria' to justify their actions, but it has done nothing to quell the endless conflict over the centuries.
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Who defines what Victoria is? Is it the sixty nomadic cities and the land around them, the forty million people that live within, or the monarch who rules them?
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Your Royal Highness Alexandrina Vina Victoria.
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Why have you come back, when you say you came back for Victoria?
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: The noble mansions have been burned to the ground. Wonder how many survivors there are...
attributes.name: Golding

attributes.content: The Sarkaz are planning something big, and the Defense Forces aren't trying to hide it anymore.
attributes.name: Golding

attributes.content: This street may never be the same again.
attributes.name: Golding

attributes.content: Golding knows that the visit from the commander means her identity is no longer a secret.
She wanders the streets aimlessly, filled with a deep feeling of helplessness.
Perhaps it was always futile for humans to fight the tide.
Adams's bookstore is open, but the familiar warm, yellow light is absent. Golding has a bad feeling.
The bookstore is empty, but the smell of blood fills every corner, so thick it might as well have taken physical form.
Golding realizes that the ground is sticky.
Not just the ground. The counter, the cashier, the books on the shelves, and the teapot that Adams always has by his side.
Everything has been painted a shade of light red.
Blood.
The nausea that has been bothering Golding for days explodes uncontrollably.
She runs out onto the streets and begins to vomit.
Are you okay?
Ughâ€”*cough*
attributes.name: Golding

attributes.content: ...Molly.
attributes.name: Golding

attributes.content: You don't look well. Here, take my shoulder.
attributes.name: Molly

attributes.content: We still have time, Lady Golding. Your part is not over yet.
attributes.name: Molly

attributes.content: You said that education was your strength, didn't you?
attributes.name: Molly

attributes.content: My strength...
attributes.name: Golding

attributes.content: Let's go back.
attributes.name: Molly

attributes.content: We've persevered for so long. We'll see this to the end.
attributes.name: Molly

attributes.content: I'm counting on you.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Don't worry, we'll get our new friends to the base safely.
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Fighter

attributes.content: You're not coming with us?
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: I have another mission.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Your grandson is a pretty big deal in the Corps, after all.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Real big deals don't usually boast about it.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Oh, and I have to return this, Granny.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Your badge.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: I'm not a worker anymore. I shouldn't be wearing this outside.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Being smart isn't enough to fool death. Those who are gone will never come back, and the wounds left behind do not necessarily fade with time.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: But I don't want to spend night after night in regret, staring at machines with no one to use them.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Because...
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I will go into each and every night.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I will carry the torch left behind by those who are gone and keep walking.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Until the cold is driven out, and the path ahead is no longer dark. And even then, I'll keep walking.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Not for some ethereal hope, not because I'm still waiting for someone to make a stand for us.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: You said it, that we built Londinium with our own hands.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Even if the city is reduced to rubble tomorrow, we'll start rebuilding it the day after.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Feist says all that in one breath.
His words are met with silence, but he finds that the silence no longer makes him anxious.
A thought comes mind as he gazes upon his grandmother, standing by the production line.
When did her hair turn so white?
Huff...
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Go, if your mind's made up.
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Let me see.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Bye, Granny.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Feist!
attributes.name: Catherine

attributes.content: Feist glimpses a small card flying towards him from the corner of his eye.
It is the badge that he just returned.
He smiles.
I'll be back, Granny.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: With victory.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I know you'll be proud of me, so there's no need to say it.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: What I really want you to know is...
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I'll be proud of this factory, no matter where I go in the future.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: And... you too.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Also, I've thought about the question you asked.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: The things that disappointed you so much, the betrayal, the suspicions, people who just can't work together... I know we'll have to face them again.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: But if knowing that means we have to abandon our trust in others... then we won't survive this war.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: We have to face it sooner or later, win or lose.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: One more thing.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I've never seen inside the suit of a Steam Knight, but I'll always remember the silhouette hammering away by the production line.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: You've always been my hero, and you always will be.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Hehe...
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Bye, for real, before this gets too awkward.
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Bang. Clang. Bang.
The production line keeps running, as though nothing has ever changed.
Feist hears a familiar sigh from deep inside the factory.
He waves without looking back, and walks into the sunlight outside.
